00:11:44.350 --> 00:11:45.475
MARK Z. DANIELEWSKI: Right.

00:11:45.475 --> 00:11:48.300
SPEAKER: So I'm interested
if the technology around us

00:11:48.300 --> 00:11:50.710
today you feel
influences the way

00:11:50.710 --> 00:11:52.455
you want to present
stories as a writer,

00:11:52.455 --> 00:11:53.830
if it influences
the way you want

00:11:53.830 --> 00:11:55.027
to communicate as a writer?

00:11:55.027 --> 00:11:56.110
MARK Z. DANIELEWSKI: Sure.

00:11:56.110 --> 00:11:59.750
I think it's-- I think my
attention has always been

00:11:59.750 --> 00:12:01.040
there.

00:12:01.040 --> 00:12:05.350
When "House of Leaves" came out,
there was very little emphasis

00:12:05.350 --> 00:12:10.940
in the at least formal literary
world on typography and image

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:13.450
and graphics.

00:12:13.450 --> 00:12:16.420
And yet that's something
that was already happening.

00:12:16.420 --> 00:12:22.150
It preceded Instagram,
and Flickr, and Tumblr,

00:12:22.150 --> 00:12:25.650
and all these things that
were sort of image-based.

00:12:25.650 --> 00:12:27.360
And I think I grew
up in a time where

00:12:27.360 --> 00:12:32.750
I watched this amazing,
kaleidoscopic shatter

00:12:32.750 --> 00:12:34.720
of platforms that
one could invest

00:12:34.720 --> 00:12:37.500
their creative or
social energies.

00:12:37.500 --> 00:12:40.610
And I think the thing
that's exciting,

00:12:40.610 --> 00:12:43.090
even though people have
their own domain, really,

00:12:43.090 --> 00:12:45.250
of where they hang
out digitally,

00:12:45.250 --> 00:12:49.290
they also sort of like to
experience other areas.

00:12:49.290 --> 00:12:54.890
And those areas begin to kind
of influence their personality.

00:12:54.890 --> 00:12:57.940
So the book itself encompasses
various perspectives

00:12:57.940 --> 00:13:01.425
that aren't merely just
these characters, but also

00:13:01.425 --> 00:13:03.950
the voice of technology
itself, the voice

00:13:03.950 --> 00:13:05.480
of these various applications.

00:13:05.480 --> 00:13:07.650
Whether it's the coding
within certain chapters,

00:13:07.650 --> 00:13:11.130
or like you pointed out,
these YouTube moments.

00:13:11.130 --> 00:13:15.150
They begin to sort of
create in one place

00:13:15.150 --> 00:13:23.300
the sound of all of these
different views and voices

00:13:23.300 --> 00:13:25.685
and hieroglyphs, I
guess, coming together.

